    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>You conjure haunting ghosts of a forgotten past into the area. When you cast the spell, you can direct the ghosts to harass one creature in the affected area, giving that creature the @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.Item.nywSVEeDvp1bk7L3]{shaken} condition for 1 round (Will negates); this is a fear effect. For the duration of the spell, the ghosts disparage, claw at, and swirl around creatures in the area, negating any miss chance against those creatures due to concealment (but not total concealment) and imposing a –5 penalty to Stealth checks attempted while in the area. This does not negate concealment altogether, and creatures in the area can still use any concealment to hide. As a move action, you can move the area up to 30 feet within the spell’s range.</p>"
